An attack helicopter is a type of helicopter specifically designed and equipped with weapons for attacking enemy targets. The attack helicopter is often used in military operations to provide close air support for ground troops. Attack helicopters are very fast and agile, making them effective in combat situations where rapid response and maneuverability are necessary. They are armed with a variety of weapons including machine guns, rockets, and missiles, which can be used to take out enemy tanks, vehicles, and infantry. The Apache is one of the most well-known and widely used attack helicopters in the world, and it has played a critical role in many conflicts.
